\\\":\\\"**Clarifying class loading behavior**\\\\n\\\\nI’m looking into the ClassLoader.loadClass contract, which states that the resulting class must have a binary name. It seems possible to return String.class without any VM checks in method overrides. The invocation in line 462 on a subclass is dynamic access, which might matter. I can implement a custom ClassLoader that overrides loadClass. The first loader fails with a made-up name, but my custom context class loader can return a real class. Line 457 succeeds with null, using loader.loadClass, and I could load UtilitiesTest.class without issues.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Assessing testing structure**\\\\n\\\\nI’m considering using a class ServiceFactory that implements Factory<String>. I might need to run a test for each call, and think about combining them for efficiency. There's a need for a coverage report for active classes, and I realize tests may cover private static classes without needing odd file names. I've got to verify if test line 462 handles MultiException correctly. It seems like there's a lot to ensure regarding class loading and error management.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Evaluating class loading in Native Image**\\\\n\\\\nI’m thinking about how the class loader in a Native Image app can trigger a ClassNotFoundException, which is good to know. Overriding the ClassLoader seems odd; can I really subclass it? I suppose that should work, but there might be limitations in ClassLoader support. While overriding loadClass seems straightforward, I'm wondering if using the ClassLoader constructor could be an option. I’m also considering whether using ClassLoader.getPlatformClassLoader as a parent is relevant.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering test mapping**\\\\n\\\\nI'm noticing that the existing Hk2_locatorTest isn't mapped, which seems like a concern. The rule states there should be a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files, so I'm wondering if it's best not to add anything extra. The user mentioned an active dynamic class, Utilities, so I'll include UtilitiesTest. The existing placeholder remains untouched, but I think the user-code-filter needs to encompass the test package properly.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_DuhY56OCq2DOPStlhlc49t5C|fc_049708e11698621b016a024583859c819f80639ece0f52e5b3\", \"name\": \"read\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-locator/2.5.0-b05/user-code-filter.json\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 679, \"output\": 1375, \"cacheRead\": 18944, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 20998, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778533739748, \"responseId\": \"resp_049708e11698621b016a02456c8f00819fa8239d13b6f5743f\"}}\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.glassfish.hk2:hk2-locator:2.5.0-b05/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-11T21-10-36-113076Z.log:1471:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating dependencies & testing order**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I need the javassist dependency, which might not be necessary for testImplementation. The hk2-locator could be optional, but if it’s missing, it affects the proxiesAvailable method. I wonder about caching issues; if prior tests run, they could disrupt execution due to the unpredictable test order. I might need to explore ways to reset the private static cache and how to make certain methods fail or succeed under specific conditions.\\n\\n**Exploring class loading scenarios**\\n\\nI'm considering that since the test class is on the same classpath, maybe the app loader can load it as well. I need to use a custom context class loader for classes not visible to Utilities. However, dynamic class loading isn't open-ended. In a Native Image, dynamic loading isn't supported, but the class exists in the image. I wonder if a custom child-first class loader could delegate to a parent properly. This presents challenges if the standard app loader can already load all test classes. Could I override loadClass to return a class for a fictitious name instead?\\n\\n**Clarifying class loading behavior**\\n\\nI’m looking into the ClassLoader.loadClass contract, which states that the resulting class must have a binary name. It seems possible to return String.class without any VM checks in method overrides. The invocation in line 462 on a subclass is dynamic access, which might matter. I can implement a custom ClassLoader that overrides loadClass. The first loader fails with a made-up name, but my custom context class loader can return a real class. Line 457 succeeds with null, using loader.loadClass, and I could load UtilitiesTest.class without issues.\\n\\n**Assessing testing structure**\\n\\nI’m considering using a class ServiceFactory that implements Factory<String>. I might need to run a test for each call, and think about combining them for efficiency. There's a need for a coverage report for active classes, and I realize tests may cover private static classes without needing odd file names. I've got to verify if test line 462 handles MultiException correctly. It seems like there's a lot to ensure regarding class loading and error management.\\n\\n**Evaluating class loading in Native Image**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how the class loader in a Native Image app can trigger a ClassNotFoundException, which is good to know. Overriding the ClassLoader seems odd; can I really subclass it? I suppose that should work, but there might be limitations in ClassLoader support. While overriding loadClass seems straightforward, I'm wondering if using the ClassLoader constructor could be an option. I’m also considering whether using ClassLoader.getPlatformClassLoader as a parent is relevant.\\n\\n**Considering test mapping**\\n\\nI'm noticing that the existing Hk2_locatorTest isn't mapped, which seems like a concern. The rule states there should be a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files, so I'm wondering if it's best not to add anything extra. The user mentioned an active dynamic class, Utilities, so I'll include UtilitiesTest. The existing placeholder remains untouched, but I think the user-code-filter needs to encompass the test package properly.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_049708e11698621b016a02456d5c58819fb00afadf08221088\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqAkWDCoy-xCVCmQmj0-qUtVR4cdX_20etMkfGBDohcQjVSW6Anstv8A3920Dwy7fww0gektmMyJyw-8MiSJxMaomYlv9m3peSUohmdVxpvkaUf1z4Lot4V_tW0o0DWYaH8ubo3_zNRY_1d9bZCsUoFhpX7gBGtgXKdvYoHe9Oar1wiqni0CykRCHy2OX53vz8p9Ooyfc0QeRhTRUs5T1Er0-Mq632GC3BJhO4Vw8DyeYWzzmlYDFOKipV-uWfbtWKoOfgzkfUx7jNNbEEvR3DhiNh9Opaq8yI4ErUdC-V8j1OF7VZ7b85BkopaQXODbA_9xXl4kB6_tCBlAzQjcemk-n87Ce5EiYTSlphjgI2BBpiSOJZXvs1l9rGU8SwfJFFO47aTndBrBBP3kl4gcTuL5aYPSShMU6TSwen87Q8LwTO6Tv5KrGhbqnWkzcQl05HYlTL8UewfDvLIu980g45gj-UYHohwXdQsER4-sK7ejpsjJzVrIqYL1f46c5yGCFCuimCkJdN3iL6YplfW5gd1pj4a6k6CGuj5SIv1VrZj6lLle-duET0sfdMu3JZF6esVdqjY45OSN9o7iDnbY587oOopPXhO-qDkMWBh453DwPlRNPda2-kOGW7YbjGfKru4D1JB4qg6MhaxQDvYG1wCFwhmPWOuQDa36GMeKlDgfwQwmO4yWo9-0A08bv8bKSiKBjScIU7ipE013Q73s40pqEzuW8btoCKOThirDeT7xkIqQi3-lBW9jPA9VCymbECSSFBST_ZEr8FerjoC9XsT8E2oz-G161YQBn8By27iS0HHKe3NqP8csM-R4iJx8r3l-KDVKjDqIP8UyafKe5j3xOvioyBhjWXZOi8V06gGI-0emWXLeLjzO8It_qihMVG4T4uMo3EyUTdl7Ws9zEO5qbXpAzJQtyAbXOWYwii2N68sWfB6iU0lzpLCYq6TA4qXdvC5UOJQjzb2PuamA1ZytqLP5oa2hj_rcStEUwxeI7j10WpJv_sVEkjQH-Wt1OE_sJmxShnZuwAiYsSu9wXQrJVKE-DTOn-aeWV4LaA3sDLA77dL2Sbk3_LM_eor1QFRDtot9ZGGGndml8MmGrS1FreCqiZWFqiKiHstcN6MDwKyMGSdLjoMxuoOFK6lIoK7JitTOTi1H8pqv61-sSf38-Bj05QlcCwA825fjLq7ZBr_WQV4e